OLAS and CALMS will be hosting the Bridging Past, Present, and Future in Latin American Health: Student Symposium event this fall!

At this event, we will be providing a medium for students to network and communicate with Latin healthcare professionals, researchers, academics, and community health workers to discuss how we can better health outcomes for the Latin American community in Toronto.
We hope to provide mentorship and support to Latin students wanting to enter a healthcare field, however this event is open to student, person, or staff interested in the conversation at hand.

The event will take place September 17, 2024 from 5-8
pm at the William Doo Auditorium.
Please sign up in the EventBrite in the link in our bio :)

If you have accessibility requirements, please email olassg@studentorg.utoronto.ca

See you there OLAS! 

#olas #calms #medicine #oft #newcollege #healthequity #mentorship #health #publichealth

⚽️ Exciting news! The Canadian Association of Latin Medical Students (CALMS) is partnering with York United FC for their exhibition game this Friday, August 16!

Cheer on your team and support a great cause — $5 from every ticket will be donated to CALMS to help achieve its mission of supporting Latin medical students and increasing diversity in professional fields! 🩺👨🏻‍⚕️👩🏽‍⚕️
